<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573426>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of a study skin of Olallamys albicaudus (AMNH [American Museum of Natural History] 36245; holotype of Thrinacodus apolinari) from Fómeque, Department of Cundinamarca, Colombia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573426/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573428>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral (inverted) views of skull and lateral view of mandible of an adult (sex unknown) Olallamys albicaudus (AMNH [American Museum of Natural History] 36245; holotype of Thrinacodus apolinari) from Fómeque, Department of Cundinamarca, Colombia; collected by Apolinar María on 7 March 1914. Condylobasal length is 50.75 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573428/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573430>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Geographic distribution of Olallamys albicaudus. Localities of sampled specimens obtained from collections records and literature are indicated by triangles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573430/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

